                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12705390" author="jmesnil" created="Wed, 11 Jul 2012 06:12:26 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;To support this property, we would need to add the ability to start/stop delivery on deployed MDB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One way to achieve this would be to add start/stopDelivery() runtime operations to the MDB resource definition and have its runtime handler implement them (they would delegate to the MDB Component start()/stop() method)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This also means that we need to have a way to do this in the web console. Currently, it is only possible to enable/disable an EAR. With this feature, we would have to find a way to also let users enable/disable individual MDBs inside the EAR. &lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12775525" author="wolfc" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 04:27:29 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;As per comments on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/HORNETQ-942&quot; title=&quot;CLONE - Hornetq adapter doesn&amp;#39;t implement ActivationConfigProperty DeliveryActive&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HORNETQ-942&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HORNETQ-942&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; this must not be an activation config property, but an administrative operation that activates / deactivates the endpoint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The initial setting can be modelled into the descriptor and if needed have its own annotation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775529" author="mlange" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 04:47:35 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Carlo, just to be sure to understand your last comment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With a setting in the descriptor (messaging/ejb subsystem?) it will be possible to set an initial value &quot;deliveryActive=false&quot; so that the message delivery is not started in the server startup process until it is activated?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775531" author="wolfc" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 04:53:41 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking of an element in jboss-ejb3.xml. And yes that could then be set to &apos;false&apos;, so the endpoint would only be activated through an administrative operation (CLI implemented at first, hopefully console later).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12786473" author="jmesnil" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2013 08:12:44 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;PR for master branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12787705" author="jira-bugzilla-migration" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 09:50:27 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Ravi Bhardwaj &amp;lt;rbhardwa@redhat.com&amp;gt; made a comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=981341&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;bug 981341&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Description of problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;startDelivery()/stopDelivery() missing in EAP 6 which were available using JMX in EAP 5.x.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12787893" author="jmesnil" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2013 10:00:46 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;PR merged in master branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
